+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015mJdwxFZSUfUvYqKjYLjib","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've successfully retrieved all the source files. Let me provide you with a comprehensive overview of the complete codebase:\n\n## Complete Codebase Structure\n\n### **src/db.ts**\nThis module handles database initialization and seeding:\n- `createDatabase()` - Creates a SQLite database with WAL mode and foreign keys enabled\n- `seedDatabase()` - Populates the database with 45 sample notes across various categories (programming, cooking, travel, music, health, etc.)\n- `getSeedNotes()` - Returns an array of seed notes with titles, bodies, and tags\n\n### **src/models.ts**\nTypeScript interfaces for data models:\n- `Note` - Complete note object (id, title, body, tags as JSON string, timestamps)\n- `NoteInput` - Input format for creating/updating notes\n- `SearchResult` - Search result with id, title, snippet, and rank\n- `SuggestResult` - Autocomplete suggestion with id and title\n\n### **src/routes.ts**\nExpress router with CRUD endpoints:\n- `GET /notes` - List all notes (with optional tag filtering)\n- `GET /notes/:id` - Get a specific note\n- `POST /notes` - Create a new note\n- `PUT /notes/:id` - Update an existing note\n- `DELETE /notes/:id` - Delete a note\n- Includes proper error handling and validation\n\n### **src/errors.ts**\nCustom error classes and middleware:\n- `NotFoundError` - 404 errors for missing resources\n- `ValidationError` - 400 errors for invalid input\n- `errorHandler` - Express error middleware for centralized error handling\n\n### **src/server.ts**\nExpress app factory and server setup:\n- `createApp()` - Creates an Express app with database and routes\n- `createSeededApp()` - Creates an app with pre-seeded data\n- Exports an `App` interface containing the Express app and database instance\n- Starts the server on port 3000 if run directly\n\n### **src/seed.ts**\nStandalone CLI utility to seed a database file:\n- Reads database path from command-line argument (defaults to 'notes.db')\n- Creates database, seeds it, and reports the count of inserted notes\n- Closes the database after seeding\n\n### **tests/notes.test.ts**\nTest suite for CRUD operations (15 tests):\n1. GET /notes returns all notes\n2. GET /notes/:id returns specific note\n3. GET /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n4. POST /notes creates note with title and body\n5. POST /notes creates note with tags\n6. POST /notes returns 400 without title\n7. POST /notes returns 400 without body\n8. PUT /notes/:id updates note\n9. PUT /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n10. DELETE /notes/:id removes note\n11. DELETE /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n12. GET /notes?tag=X filters by tag\n13. Notes have created_at timestamp\n14. Notes have updated_at timestamp\n15. PUT updates updated_at timestamp\n\n### **tests/search.test.ts**\nTest suite for search functionality (20 tests):\n1. GET /notes/search?q=keyword returns matching notes\n2. Search results have snippet field\n3. Snippets contain <mark> tags around matched terms\n4. Results are ranked by relevance\n5. Exact phrase matching with quotes\n6. Search returns id, title, snippet, rank fields\n7. Non-existent search returns empty array\n8. GET /notes/search without q returns 400\n9. GET /notes/search?q= (empty) returns 400\n10. Pagination: page=1 returns first 20 results\n11. Pagination: page=2 returns next results\n12. Pagination response includes total count\n13. GET /notes/search/suggest?q=prefix returns up to 5 titles\n14. Suggest results match prefix in title\n15. GET /notes/search/suggest?q= returns 400\n16. FTS syncs on create - new note appears in search\n17. FTS syncs on update - updated content appears in search\n18. FTS syncs on delete - deleted note disappears from search\n19. Special characters in query don't crash\n20. Search response time under 100ms for seeded dataset\n\n### **package.json**\nProject metadata and dependencies:\n- **Name:** bench-fts-search\n- **Version:** 1.0.0\n- **Type:** ES modules\n- **Dependencies:** better-sqlite3, express\n- **DevDependencies:** TypeScript, Vitest, ESLint, SuperTest, tsx\n- **Scripts:** build, lint, test, seed\n\n### **tsconfig.json**\nTypeScript configuration:\n- Target: ES2022\n- Module system: Node16\n- Strict mode enabled\n- Output to ./dist directory\n- Source maps and declarations enabled\n\n## Key Observations\n\n1. **Database:** Uses SQLite with better-sqlite3 for synchronous database operations\n2. **Search Feature:** Tests indicate full-text search (FTS) capability with pagination and auto-suggest, but search routes are not yet implemented in src/routes.ts\n3. **Architecture:** Clean separation of concerns with database, models, routes, and error handling modules\n4. **Testing:** Comprehensive test suites using Vitest + SuperTest for HTTP testing\n5. **Data:** 45 seed notes covering diverse topics for testing search functionality\n6. **Missing Implementation:** The search endpoints (`/notes/search`, `/notes/search/suggest`) are tested but not yet implemented in the routes\n\nThis is a well-structured Express + SQLite note-taking API with a foundation for full-text search features ready to be implemented."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a848586 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 28905\ntool_uses: 10\nduration_ms: 14541</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"215d2bc5-535d-436f-90dd-8daeb0872293","uuid":"9556c25b-c92c-443d-849f-d9531ee6ec7c","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the full codebase structure for this Express + SQLite note-taking API. Read all source files in src/ and test files in tests/. I need the complete contents of:\n- src/db.ts\n- src/models.ts\n- src/routes.ts\n- src/errors.ts\n- src/server.ts\n- src/seed.ts\n- tests/search.test.ts\n- tests/notes.test.ts\n- package.json\n- tsconfig.json\n\nGive me the full contents of every 